<br>
The Mercenary class could use some thematic or contextual polish IMO. Specifically, by making our abilities all pull in the same direction. I.e. compliment each other. That's what makes an attractive class. Right now we have all these little active hang-nail abilities that just take up weight on the scales and allow Mythic to just keep pointing at them when they need a reason not to do anything more for the merc. Flurry and Charge come immediately to mind.<br>
<br>
A specific suggestion:<br>
<br>
Scrap Flurry and Charge and then create and give us Advanced Parry. I.e. 360 degree parry. We ARE dual wielders, after all. And it just seems more feasible, anyway, that someone could swing their off weapon around and catch incoming blows easier than they could move their whole body.<br>
(Who in the world thought of Advanced Evade complimenting Evade I?)<br>
<br>
If that suggestion brings up the hymned &quot;but mercs are an offensive class&quot; statement, then I would propose some more passive Merc-specific offensive abilities:<br>
 <br>
* An innately and significantly higher chance to crit, exclusive to mercs.<br>
 <br>
* More than one kind of &quot;Dirty Tricks&quot;. How about something like &quot;Side Swipe&quot; a side positioned knee to the thigh, or similar, that debuffs Dex or Quickness. Or &quot;Low Blow&quot; a stout kick to the groin that causes a delay in the target's melee even if the target has been stunned to death already. Something like that could be on a long DW style chain, if need be. Or how about a back positional called &quot;Wedgie&quot; that....just kidding. Being serious though, it would be cool to have two or even three different types of Dirty Tricks to use, given the mostly offensive role we're supposed to have. And damn it'd be nice to have something like that as styles and not as more little mini active abilities.<br>
<br>
* A long chained Style that lets us hit multiple opponents like the savages have. NOT a 30 min timered PBAoE. Hell, base it off of Evade. THAT would maybe make Evade I sit better with some people.<br>
<br>
* OR at least the ability to trade health for endurance. Since we're somewhat cast as a charging, howling determined fighter class.<br>
<br>
And lastly, one suggestion for Charge if they decide to never remove that curse from the Merc: Change it to where we not only get the free 10 seconds of sprinting after an enemy, but during that time we can't be rooted, or snared, or slowed. It IS a charge after all.<br>
<br>
That's all. Thanks for all your patience and good luck with your future feedback reports. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
