<br>
I think a few of us here are pushing for an advanced parry and trying to come up with some more 'offensively attuned' abilites for the dirty tricks line...<br>
<br>
Mythic has said that they'd like to do more things to parry, as mentioned in the recent feedback... So I doubt anything else will happen to parry for anyone at least until they can do what they have planned for it...<br>
<br>
There are just alot of things that could be changed and made more useful... Alot of other things that could be added to benifit our class... And a few other things that should never be changed...<br>
<br>
Despite all of that though, I am proud of my Merc as is... He can stand his own in RvR combat, with about a 50% survival rate in 1 on 1 fights (Except for those damned Enchanters, HINT: If you see a solo 'chanter and you're alone, look the other way unless you really take him/her by surprise, if he/she sees you running at them; 'sick pet and run' is their tactic... Continue chasing them? The pet kills you, stop and attack the pet? You're nuked 50 times if you survive that long - /end rant) and maybe a 20% survival rate in group fights... He dies alot, yes, but when he does I had caused the enemy's life to flashes before his eyes to the point of a touch would equal death... We are the most stylish class in the game, so at least we die beautifully...<br>
<br>
